description.plain:
Nick Simmons (born December 18, 1999), more commonly known as YBN Nahmir, is an American rapper from Birmingham, Alabama.

Nahmir found acclaim when WorldStarHipHop posted his video for “Rubbin Off The Paint” to YouTube. The viral video received over two million views in just three days.

Since then he has continued to pursue music, gain millions of listeners, and help his fellow YBN members on to the music scene, such as YBN Almighty Jay and YBN Cordae.

description.plain:
On “Rubbin Off The Paint,” YBN Nahmir raps about getting wealthy and his savage behavior.

This song became a minor hit for YBN which debuted at #78 and peaked at #46 on the Billboard Hot 100. The music video—released on September 18, 2017—has amassed over 156 million views and shows no sign of stopping.

songs.full_title: Bounce Out With That by YBN Nahmir
songs.title: Bounce Out With That

description.plain:
This is the follow-up to YBN Nahmir’s viral hit, “Rubbin’ off the Paint.” Paying homage to Bobby Shmurda’s runaway single “Hot Nigga” on the hook, YBN Nahmir lets us know he’s serious about coming for his competition, before going on to cover familiar territory about being irresistible to women and hustling.

The corresponding video was directed by Cole Bennett and featured a cameo from Philly rapper PnB Rock. The video racked up 13 million hits in its first week.
